cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.LG

The paper discusses the application of monotonic abstraction techniques in model checking distributed systems and software. This makes it likely to belong to the following sub-categories:

- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper discusses logical techniques such as quantifier relativizations and instantiations, which are relevant to this sub-category.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper discusses the use of CEGAR loops in software model checking, which is a topic relevant to this sub-category.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the application of model checking techniques to software, which is a topic relevant to this sub-category.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory): The paper discusses the verification of distributed systems, which can be modeled using formal languages and automata theory.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): While not a primary focus of the paper, the use of over-approximation techniques in model checking could be relevant to this sub-category.
